safekeeping. Who acts like this outside of guests on ``Springer''?
Any young women you know?
</P>
<P>
   Me neither.
</P>
<P>
   Lewinsky's crass behavior and Clinton's lewd behavior aside, I
still say it's Hillary who should be outraged, not a special
prosecutor or Congress. Even as I see the familiar Republican faces
blabbing on TV about impeachment, even as I sort through the daily
barrage of E-mail messages from Clinton-bashers who must have the
phrases ``suborning perjury,'' ``lying under oath'' and ``moral
issue'' on their computer's save-get keys, I want to stand on a
mountaintop and scream:
</P>
<P>
   ARE WE ALL INSANE OR WHAT?!?!?!?
</P>
<P>
   A long time ago, Kenneth Starr launched an investigation into
the Whitewater matter _ and somehow that led him to a McCarthyesque
witch-hunt that's so ludicrous it defies belief. While we're still
inside this chapter of history, I want to go on record as saying
this is a ridiculous, embarrassing investigation that should have
been abandoned a long time ago. Even if Clinton and Lewinsky were
to hold a joint press conference today to announce they're in love
and they intend to marry someday, it still wouldn't be cause for
impeachment.
</P>
<P>
   But there's nothing any of us can do to stop this rollercoaster
from completing its course. The stories will keep on coming, the
leaks will keep on leaking, and sometime in the near future the
country will be told exactly what caused the stain on that garment
of Ms. Lewinsky's.
</P>
<P>
   She's not too skinny, she's not too fat, she's a real humdinger
and I like 'em like that! Devil with the blue dress, blue dress,
blue dress, devil with the blue dress on...
</P>
<P>
   &UR; (Richard Roeper (rroeper &LR; suntimes.com) can be heard on the
``Media Creatures'' show, which airs daily in Chicago from 10 a.m.
to 2 p.m. on WMVP-AM (1000) and appears Tuesday and Thursday at
7:55 a.m. on WFLD-TV's ``Fox Thing in the Morning.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; (A daily columnist for the Chicago Sun-Times, Roeper has also
written for TV Guide, Spy, Playboy, Chicago magazine and many other
publications, and has appeared as a guest on ``Nightline'' and
``Oprah.'') &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ---------------- &QC;
</P>
