<P>
   HISPANICS _ WASHINGTON - The Hispanic population in the United
States is nearing 30 million, or almost 11 percent of the total, a
trend that puts them well on their way to becoming the nation's
largest ethnic group, according to the latest report from the
Census Bureau. The report also shows that more than half were born
in the United States, raising questions about the practice of
viewing Hispanics as an immigrant population. (Shepard, Cox News
Service).
</P>
