<P>
   YAGER _ ATLANTA _ Faye Yager and husband Howard are the subjects
of a hearing in federal court Thursday. A Connecticut man has sued
the Yagers for hiding his son in their ``underground'' of allegedly
abused children. Hearing is for temporary restraining order to halt
the Yager's ``organized lawlessness'' and have them tell Jeffery
Rubenstein where he can find his son. Rubenstein was awarded
custody of the boy and through lengthy divorce and custody fights
there was never any claims he abused the boy. Bonnie Rubenstein
first made claims of abuse when she came to see Faye Yager.
(Williams, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
