   SCHOOLS-ROAST _ AUSTIN, Texas _ While most students are stocking
up on school supplies, Austin school bus driver Ida Collins is
freezing bottles of water in preparation for the first day of
school. Local meteorologists say it probably won't cool off until
September. Until then, students will trudge to and from school
beneath blazing skies, swelter on school buses without air
conditioning and sweat their way through outdoor athletic
practices. (Alford, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
