 Attn Sports Editors:  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Sports stories in sight at this hour from The New York Times
News Service for  &UR; FRIDAY &LR; , Aug. 7.
</P>
<P>
   BBA-ANDERSON-COLUMN (Undated) _ Sports of The Times column: The
Yankees aren't playing against other American League teams anymore.
For the rest of the season, they'll be playing the ghosts of a team
that existed nearly a century ago. As the Yankees returned to the
Stadium today with an 80-29 record, they're chasing the 1906
Chicago Cubs that won a record 116 games. But who are those `06
ghosts. And how did they do it? By Dave Anderson.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-METS-GIANTS (New York) _ San Francisco at the Mets, 12:10
p.m. By Jason Diamos.
</P>
<P>
   Other baseball as needed.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-JETS-EAGLES (Philadelphia) _ N.Y. Jets at Philadelphia
Eagles in NFL exhibition football. By Gerald Eskenazi.
</P>
<P>
   Other football as needed.
</P>
<P>
   For information and repeats call the News Service at (888)
346-9867. And be sure to look for other sports stories from our
partners: Bloomberg News, The Boston Globe, Cox News Service,
Hearst News Service, The Houston Chronicle, The Arizona Republic,
Kansas City Star, Fort Worth Star-Telegram, Los Angeles Daily News,
San Francisco Chronicle and Seattle Post-Intelligencer.
