   CONGO-REBELLION (Abidjan, Ivory Coast) _ Rebels in the Congo on
Thursday seized control of a strategic oil port in the far west,
according to rebel spokesmen and foreign diplomats, significantly
widening their campaign to wrest power from President Laurent
Kabila. By Howard W. French. With map.
