   RENO-CONTEMPT (Washington) _ A House investigating committee
voted Thursday along party lines to charge Attorney General Janet
Reno with contempt of Congress because she refuses to give the
committee memorandums from the top Justice Department investigators
of campaign finance abuses. By David E. Rosenbaum.
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-STARR (Washington) _ Monica Lewinski testifies before
one of Kenneth Starr's grand juries about her relationship with
President Clinton. Other developments in the investigation. By
James Bennet.
</P>
<P>
   With: CLINTON-LEWINSKI (Washington) _ For six months she's been
a virtual prisoner in her own home, but with her appearance
Thursday before the grand jury, Monica Lewinski takes the first
step toward resuming a life free of lawyers, publicists and a daily
recounting of the most personal details of a private relationship
turned public. By Melinda Henneberger.
</P>
