<HEADER>
A1432 &Cx1f; tad-z
r i &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-NEVIS-BOX-$ADV09-COX     08-06 0295
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-NEVIS-BOX-$ADV09-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    FACTS AND FIGURES ABOUT ST. KITTS-NEVIS
 &HT;    With NEVIS-SECEDE-$ADV09.
 &HT;    For Use Sunday, Aug. 9 And Thereafter.
 &HT;    By SHELLEY EMLING 
 &HT;    c.1998 Cox News Service 
<TEXT>
<P>
   St. Kitts-Nevis at-a-glance:
</P>
<P>
   (For purposes of a locator map: About 225 miles east of Puerto
Rico, in the Leeward Islands chain of the Caribbean. Separated from
St. Kitts by the two-mile Narrows Channel.)
</P>
<P>
   Size: 36 square miles.
</P>
<P>
   Population: About 11,000 people.
</P>
<P>
   Biggest city: Charlestown.
</P>
<P>
   Claim to fame: Birthplace of U.S. founding father, Alexander
Hamilton.
</P>
<P>
   Biggest employer: The Four Seasons Resort Hotel, with more than
700 workers.
</P>
<P>
   Language: English.
</P>
<P>
   Currency: Eastern Caribbean dollar, although U.S. dollar is
widely accepted.
</P>
<P>
   Economy: Upscale tourism; offshore financial services.
</P>
<P>
   Hotel rooms: 482 on Nevis, which includes 196 at Four Seasons;
and 985 on St. Kitts.
</P>
<P>
   Status: Part of the two-island federation of St. Kitts and
Nevis, total population 44,000 -- 11,000 on Nevis. The federation
became the newest and smallest independent country in the Western
Hemisphere when it won independence from Britain in 1983.
</P>
<P>
   Government: Constitutional monarchy with an elected National
Assembly that has 11 seats, of which three are from Nevis and eight
are from St. Kitts. Nevis also has a separate legislature. Nevis is
headed by Premier Vance Armory, while Prime Minister Denzil Douglas
heads the federal government.
</P>
<P>
   Political parties: People's Action Movement; St. Kitts and Nevis
Labor Party; Nevis Reformation Party; and the Concerned Citizens
Movement.
</P>
<P>
   Source: St. Kitts-Nevis government.
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
