new Storm drink into additional markets. The first of five animated
commercials that continue Sprite's ``Obey your Thirst'' slogan will
begin airing next week. They were developed by Chicago-based agency
Burrell Communications Group. Coca-Cola didn't disclose how much it
was spending on the new ads. (Gramig, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   SUNBEAM _ DELRAY BEACH, Fla. _ Sunbeamannounces that it will
restate earnings for the first quarter of1998, all of 1997 and
possibly all of 1996. Also, second quarter 1998earnings will not be
released until September when the books are allstraightened out.
(Waresh, Palm Beach Post)
</P>
<P>
   DELI _ Trend story on supermarket chains now offeringseating in
their deli sections. Used to be you could order a sandwichat the
Publix deli but you had to eat it on the go. Now you can ordera
sandwich _ or hot meals _ and sit at a table right there in
themiddle of the store to eat it. Publix, Winn Dixie and Albertsons
haveall included such areas in their newest stores in Palm Beach
County,and retirees especially seem to be taking advantage of the
areas togather, eat and meet. We're finding out how profitable they
are forbusinesses. (Herubin, Palm Beach Post). WITH PHOTO.
</P>
