LEIBOWITZ-COLUMN (Undated) - The chubby young woman in the midnight
blue suit steps into daylight and takes rushed strides toward
Prettyman Courthouse. Inside, she will testify for 23 grand jurors.
The thought is, the young woman bears important answers, answers to
rattle a nation. The reality is, Monica Lewinsky bears only
questions. Questions like these you rarely hear on television,
because they do not concern bodily fluids or the presidential
groin. These questions depress, perplex, frighten. By DAVID
LEIBOWITZ. Story will move in the ``K'' category. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
