<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are the business news stories the Los Angeles Daily News
plans to move for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs
of Friday, Aug. 7 and thereafter. The stories will carry the ``f''
financial news category code unless otherwise noted. For questions
about stories, contact James Laurin at the Daily News, (818)
713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   MGM-MERGER (Los Angeles) _ Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer Inc., which has
gone from Hollywood's most powerful player to its most consistent
money-loser, announced that its days as a stand-alone studio may be
over. By Dave McNary.
</P>
<P>
   FORD-ROADBLOCK (Los Angeles) _ Ford Motor Co.'s plan to
establish a network of local dealers featuring a new superstore in
suburban Burbank as the centerpiece has hit a major roadblock. But
BertBoeckmann, the nation's top Ford retailer and a key player in
the project, issued a statement saying the superstore might still
be built. By Gregory J. Wilcox.
</P>
