<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR FRIDAY, AUGUST 7
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Friday. Days and dates refer to the original article's transmission
by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be adjusted by
NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-CONGO-NYT (moved on Wednesday, August 5)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, August
5, about the rebellion in Congo misidentified the organization that
a rebel leader, Arthur Zaidy Ngoma, once worked for. It is the
United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization,
not the United Nations Children's Fund.
</P>
<P>
   BC-SCI-BOTANY-RAVEN-NYT (moved on Monday, August 3)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, August 3,
about Dr. Peter S. Raven, director of the Missouri Botanical
Garden, misstated the size of the staff of the New York Botanical
Garden. The New York garden has 547 employees, not about 100. The
Missouri garden has 354.
</P>
