<HEADLINE>
QUOTATION OF THE DAY
</HEADLINE>
 (Eds.: This quotation refers to BC-INTERNET-SECURITY-NYT, which
moved in ``f'' news file.) 
c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``Today there is a growing trade-off between convenience and
security. By making it easy to launch a program with a single
click, you're also making it possible to launch a dangerous program
with a single click.''
</P>
<P>
   _EDWARD FELTEN, Internet security expert.
</P>
</TEXT>
