The statue of Adm. David Farragut in Manhattan's Madison Square
Park. New York City gave Farragut $50,000 to buy a home after his
Civil War successes. The pedestal to this early Saint-Gaudens
masterpiece, a sort of swirling triptych with two curving flanks,
